Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Assistant 4 Floater - Part-Time Mississauga , ON Description Job SummaryProvide customer service, reference, readers' advisory, and programs. In the absence of more senior staff, is responsible for the library location or department.Duties and ResponsibilitiesProvide reference and readers' advisoryProvide circulation services to customers, including cash handlingParticipate in supervision, scheduling, training and/or evaluationIn the absence of more senior staff, is responsible for the library location or department including staff, facility, and health and safetyCoordinate, plan, and conduct programs, class visits, tours, outreachPrepare payroll, attendance, and financial reportsCoordinate and perform duties such as, collection maintenance, inventories, supplies, financial records, holds, art exhibits, displays and room bookings.Participate on system-wide task teams and/or special projects or events.Prepare reports and statisticsResponsible for fostering a positive and respectful workplaceOther duties as assigned.Skills and QualificationsSecondary school graduation plus 3 years library experience, or a university degree/post-secondary library diploma with some library experience.Excellent customer service skillsExcellent interpersonal skills are essential in dealing with the staff and publicEffective written and oral skills in English are essentialDemonstrated keyboarding abilityAbility to lead othersExtensive knowledge in the use of library electronic resourcesComputer skills are required in relevant softwareAbility to identify process improvements and efficiencies, and lead implementation of changesLifting is involvedAvailable to work at all Mississauga Library locationsAvailable to work a minimum of 28 hours per week within library hours of work in blocks of a minimum of 4 hours (excluding Sunday).Hours of work to include evenings and SaturdaysSunday work may be requiredPlease note: This is a bargaining unit position. CUPE Local 1989 members will be given consideration for this vacancy, as per the collective agreement, followed by all other employees.Prospective applicants should consult article 16.05 of the Collective Agreement under job postings.To apply, please visit the link: Library Assistant 4 Floater Compensation $31.02 - $37.35 per hour Closes: 21 October, 2024 City of Mississauga Mississauga , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
