position is ideally suited to someone with patience, who likes working with people of all ages, who is adaptable and can multi-task, who is calm under pressure, and who enjoys and has the ability to troubleshoot technology related questions and problems.The preferred candidate will have: a certificate or diploma in Library studies or computer information technology or systems; and open availability, particularly on Sundays and Mondays. Proficiency in Farsi or Mandarin will be considered an asset.Please include your availability in a cover letter or resume. The successful candidate will be required to supply a police information check and a copy of their credentials.This posting does not list all the duties of the position, nor does it fully detail the required skills, knowledge and abilities, licenses and certificates required of candidates. For details please refer to the Class Specification which is available for inspection in the Human Resources Department or on Westnet.Position Status:Union (WVMEA) – Casual Hours of Work:Hours and days of work may vary (less than 19 hours per week)Starting Rate of Pay:$29.20 per hour plus 14% in lieu of benefits(This position has a pay structure with five steps which increase after certain hours.)Closing Date:11:59 p.m. on Sunday October 20, 2024To Apply:Please visit the District of West Vancouver’s Career Centre at westvancouver.ca/careers to apply for this position.We want to thank all applicants, however only those chosen for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $29.20 per hour plus 14% in lieu of benefits Closes: 20 October, 2024 West Vancouver Memorial Library West Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
