pus needs. We are looking for someone who will collaborate with colleagues and interact with students, faculty, and members of the community. This role will work closely with a small team at the Squamish CapU campus to provide library services that align with program development at this location. You will report to the University Librarian and receive direction from the Library Services Supervisor.What you’ll bringCompletion of a two-year Library Technology Diploma comparable to the programs offered at Langara College and the University of the Fraser Valley.Three years of related library experience, including at least two years of customer service experience.For more information For more information, please see the complete job description. For more information on the University’s vision visit Envisioning 2030 – Capilano University Take a virtual tour of our campus here: Visit CapU – Capilano UniversityBenefitsAt Capilano University, we understand that there is more to life than work. That is why we offer comprehensive benefits and support to help you and your family live a balanced life. Take a sneak peek to see what it is like to work at Capilano University. If we could make the application process more accessible for you, or if you have any questions, please contact Christina Neigel at ChristinaNeigel@capilanou.caPosting Detail InformationDays and Hours of Work Work week: 17.5 hours per week Mon-Friday at the Squamish Capilano University Campus with hours may be subject to change. There may be occasional need to attend other CapU campuses for the purpose of training and meeting activity.Pay Group 20Salary $33.46 per hourUnion MoveUPJob Open Date 09/03/2024Job Close Date 10/31/2024Open Until Filled YesQuick Link for Posting https://jobs-capilanou.peopleadmin.com/postings/7428 Compensation $33.46 per hour Closes: 31 October, 2024 Capilano University - Library North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
